{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-excerpt-js","path":"/excerpts/nature_autumn_evenings_poem/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The crunch from a carpet of leaves,<br>\nHaunts steps while canopied by trees,<br>\nA refreshing easterly breeze,<br>\nGently whipping up memories,<br>\nAs chills strive to sink their way in,<br>\nThoughts turn to the warmth that's waiting,<br>\nDays where the sun has reign have been,<br>\nNow on we see darkness growing,<br>\nIn those dying moments of day,<br>\nWe'll pray to in the moment stay,<br>\nBreathing nature's scents of decay,<br>\nWoollen garments keeps cold at bay,<br>\nRegrets not coupled with what's been,<br>\nWhile caught up in what is passing,<br>\nThough these days may warm one within,<br>\nA fire shall begin beckoning.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 07, 2020","title":"Autumn Evenings","audio":{"publicURL":"/static/c12ad9125c07387763888be5d616e81d/Christian Lacdael - Nature - 07 Autumn Evenings.mp3"},"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/e4bee9f90929ea04b77455bdb5d8d1d3/7d509/poem_on_nature_autumn_evenings.jpg","srcSet":"/static/e4bee9f90929ea04b77455bdb5d8d1d3/f836f/poem_on_nature_autumn_evenings.jpg 200w,\n/static/e4bee9f90929ea04b77455bdb5d8d1d3/2244e/poem_on_nature_autumn_evenings.jpg 400w,\n/static/e4bee9f90929ea04b77455bdb5d8d1d3/7d509/poem_on_nature_autumn_evenings.jpg 720w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/excerpts/nature_autumn_evenings_poem/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}